text.section:
A regional park authority is authorized to:
Levy taxes and issue bonds;
Accept donations, land, and equipment;
Reject unusable or unmanageable land donations;
Hire employees and contract for services; and
Enter into agreements with public and private entities under the provisions of the Interlocal Cooperation Act, KRS 65.210 to 65.300, and contracts authorizing the use of private facilities for public recreation.
